SIMPLE: million
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Million
<hw>Mil"lion</hw> <pr>(m⟦icr⟧l"y⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.,
from LL. <ets>millio</ets>, fr. L. <ets>mille</ets> a thousand. See
<er>Mile</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The number of ten hundred
thousand, or a thousand thousand, -- written 1,000,000. See the Note
under <er>Hundred</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A very great number; an indefinitely large
number.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Millions</qex> of truths that a man is not concerned to
know.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The mass of common people; -- with the article
<xex>the</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For the play, I remember, pleased not the <qex>million</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Millionaire</ent>⟦br⟧
